OL,3,CSurvey shows 60% of Britons getting no
OL,4,Cmore than six hours' sleep a night
OL,6,FAround 60% of Britons are getting no
OL,7,Fmore than six hours of sleep a night,
OL,8,Fa new survey suggests.
OL,10,FThe findings come despite NHS
OL,11,Fguidelines suggesting that a healthy
OL,12,Fadult usually needs between seven and
OL,13,Fnine hours.
OL,15,FMore than four fifths of people (83%)
OL,16,Fsay that getting a regular, good
OL,17,Fnight's sleep is the most important
OL,18,Ffactor in their general wellbeing, the
OL,19,Fpoll for wool bedding firm Woolroom
OL,20,Ffound.
