OL,3,CSurvey shows 60% of Britons getting no
OL,4,Cmore than six hours' sleep a night
OL,6,FTwo fifths of those polled (40%)
OL,7,Freported heightened stress levels
OL,8,Fafter a bad night's sleep and 36% said
OL,9,Fthey felt anxious.
OL,11,FThe survey found 40% respondents felt
OL,12,Fthis way one to two times a week,
OL,13,Fwhile 7% have this feeling constantly.
OL,14,FSome 22% said they had sought
OL,15,Fprofessional help due to the ongoing
OL,16,Feffects of poor sleep.
