OL,3,CSurvey shows 60% of Britons getting no
OL,4,Cmore than six hours' sleep a night
OL,6,FFluctuating in temperature was one of
OL,7,Fthe main causes of disrupted sleep,
OL,8,Freported by 20% of respondents, while
OL,9,F24% said they were unable to get
OL,10,Fcomfortable and 23% said stress
OL,11,Fprevented them from sleeping.
OL,13,FOne in 10 said their partner's snoring
OL,14,Fkept them awake. Woolroom found peri-
OL,15,Fmenopausal and menopausal women are
OL,16,Flosing on average more than two hours
OL,17,Fsleep a night ` or roughly two nights
OL,18,Fsleep per week due to their symptoms.
